I"<div class="p">What pain, Prometheus, O what pain</div>
<div class="p">Should wait upon thy liver's swain;</div>
<div class="p">And should he fall from ruddy skies</div>
<div class="p">O what joy behold his demise?</div>
<div class="p">Forever mourning on thy rood,</div>
<div class="p">Hard driving spikes through raptor's food,</div>
<div class="p">Thine eyes no other place can be:</div>
<div class="p">Thy thoughts on tempered Lord's decree.</div>
<div class="p">Justly punished for mercy felt,</div>
<div class="p">Wed fast to rock, a worthless pelt,</div>
<div class="p">Thy breath so vigorous before</div>
<div class="p">Is ragged now, and in short store.</div>
<div class="p">Would thou warm each cheerless child,</div>
<div class="p">Face the stormy Lightning riled</div>
<div class="p">And as thou pluck his sleeping coal</div>
<div class="p">Damn thy uncertain pagan soul?</div>
<div class="p">Thy mothers love is pure and strong</div>
<div class="p">And thusly sounds the deathly gong;</div>
<div class="p">As Zeus proclaims thy tenured fate</div>
<div class="p">Thy lips are parted: 'I can wait.'</div>
<div class="p">As keenly 'garded ages pass</div>
<div class="p">Thy mind thrice hardens, numbed as glass</div>
<div class="p">When thro' baptismal fires there</div>
<div class="p">It passes into lusty air.</div>
<div class="p">But when thy pride is shattered full</div>
<div class="p">Zeus's anger cannot but lull:</div>
<div class="p">And thus thy liberty is found;</div>
<div class="p">And to thy will thy fate is bound</div>
